<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-323-378  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 323 378.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Publish!andP;  May 1990 v5 n5 p105(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Throw it a curve: TypeAlign. (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Matsumoto, Allen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>TypeAlign, $99.95 from Emerald City Software, is a desk accessorythat works with Adobe Type Manager (ATM) to provide page layout,word processing, and illustration programs with text handlingfeatures.andP;  TypeAlign lets users set single-line heads along arcs,angles and freehand curves.andP;  It can produce EPS files that remainsmooth on screen, it has excellent kerning control, it providessuch special effects as text distortion, and it has flashyon-screen color.andP;  TypeAlign's shortcomings are minor: it only doessingle-line heads, freehand baselines are hard to edit, its colorhandling and lack of Pantone color selection limit its usefulness,and there are no keyboard shortcuts for viewing levels and toolselection.andP;  TypeAlign is well thought out, is easy to use, has avery complete online help file, and compensates for shortcomingsin text formatting that are found in many publishing programs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Emerald City Software (products).andO;Product:   TypeAlign (Computer graphics software) (evaluation)TypeAlign (Computer graphics software).andO;Topic:     Graphics SoftwareFunctional CapabilitiesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   At a glance: TypeAlign typography program. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>